"This means that the resistance of the asphalt on the roads is not uniform, but changes in one day depending on the weather conditions and temperature fluctuations," explained the chemical engineer.
The researcher of the FQ noted that the streets of Mexico City had a majority of flexible pavements composed of six layers of material, the last three of which included asphalt.
Between the top layers lies a wear layer of asphalt, which consists of small asphalted and then fortified stones.
